\subsection{Newform}
\begin{definition}\label{cmf.newform}
\uses{cmf.fouriercoefficients,cmf.hecke_operator,cmf.newspace}
A **newform** is a cusp form $f\in S_k^{\rm new}(N,\chi)$ in the {{KNOWL('cmf.newspace', 'new subspace')}} that is also an eigenform of all {{KNOWL('cmf.hecke_operator', 'Hecke operators')}}, normalized so that the {{KNOWL('cmf.fouriercoefficients', '$q$-expansion')}}  $f(z)=\sum a_n q^n$, where $q=e^{2\pi i z}$, begins with the coefficient $a_1=1$.  The newforms are a basis for the new subspace.
\end{definition}


